{"TopicId":136993,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"KSP compatible Mars Heightmap","CreatedByName":"KerikBalm","CreatedById":91917,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-15T09:31:46Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"KerikBalm","CreatedById":91917,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-15T09:31:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello all,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was wondering if anyone had a mars heightmap that I could use with kopernicus, to add \u0022mars\u0022 to KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI found these:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022elevation_2d_map_Mars_topography_MOLA_04\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022500\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.asu.cas.cz/~bezdek/vyzkum/rotating_3d_globe/figures/elevation_2d_map_Mars_topography_MOLA_04_GMT_wysiwygcont_px0650.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Mars_Global_Topo_PIA02035.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022637\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/d/d9/Mars_Global_Topo_PIA02035.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022topo_labeled.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://mola.gsfc.nasa.gov/images/topo_labeled.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut all except the 2nd one are quite far from a format that I could use with copernicus (unless I just off the poles in the last one, and removed the text).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d also have to convert it to greyscale with intensity corresponding to the color... which I\u0027m not sure I can do.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHas anyone already done something like this? Does anyone have a file I could use?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNever Mind, I think this will work \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will try on Tuesday\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002214607535641068947279.85413.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.mapaplanet.org/explorer/maps/14607535641068947279.85413.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-15T20:53:02Z\u0022 title=\u002204/15/2016 08:53  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 15, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by KerikBalm\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"legoclone09","CreatedById":142607,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-15T16:01:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReal Solar System has Mars in the game, you might be able to just install Mars.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerikBalm","CreatedById":91917,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-15T20:56:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh, well, that could simplify things a lot... now I just need to scale it down, and add an ocean like I did to duna... then move it to kerbin pseudo-L5\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m looking forward to something like this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022maxresdefault.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vX9qnJKKJks/maxresdefault.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}